author: pburba
msg: Merge r1441810 from ^/subversion/trunk.
* src-branch-1.7.x: Mergeinfo changes only
* subversion/libsvn_client/merge.c: Clean merge of r1441810.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/merge_tests.py
(conflict_aborted_mergeinfo_described_partial_merge): r1441810 replaced
the earlier version of this test, which used text conflicts, with an
expanded version that used property conflicts to resolve the issue
raised here: http://svn.haxx.se/dev/archive-2013-02/0001.shtml
Unfortunately, 1.7.x has unrelated problems with property conflicts: It
doesn't abort the merge if it encounters them!  It merrily plugs along
sans any "One or more conflicts were produced while merging...resolve
all conflicts and rerun the merge to apply the remaining unmerged
revisions" error.  So while r1441810 is a valid fix (IMO) its test fails
for unrelated reasons.  So I reworked the earlier version of test to
demonstrate the problem r1441810 fixes, but using file conflicts.

author: rajith
msg: QPID-4566 Allow a non UUID String to be set as message-id. This is
required when Qpid Messages are sent using a 3rd party JMS Message
Producer. Ex a Message Bridge. This doesn't
affect AMQP 0-10 compliance as the sender implementation will always
assign an UUID string as the message-id.
